"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody, I'm gonna be selling my garden vegetables at the farmer's market soon, and one of the reasons I am doing this is because I feel like my vegetables, my garden vegetables, are qualitatively different. They're better for you than the supermarket stuff that's grown with conventional agricultural methods. The reason I think that is because I'm using compost as opposed to fertilizers to feed the plants the nutrients and the nitrogen and all the other different things that they need. Because it's not just a generic uh nutrient formula that you give them. The the microorganisms that feed the plant through the rhizosphere are giving them very specific forms of the proteins and the carbohydrates that they need. And what they're doing with this is they're custom fitting these foods to the plant, and this imparts health benefits, but I think it also creates a structural difference in the plant itself, that the plant's DNA is actually different from the DNA of another plant because the prokaryotes in the microflora are constantly changing up their DNA profile to fit the world better. And so this activity, this dynamicism will change how the proteins fold that are given to the plants, and this is kind of what distinguishes proteins is the way that they're folded and it makes them all very, very unique. And the microflora that feeds these plants creates these folds just for the plant, and just so that the plant can absorb them and create the healthiest plant and the strongest plant, the most resistant plant from the decay cycle. And I think all of this uh DNA difference, even though it's very small, has a cumulative effect when you eat it, because all of this starts to create your biomatter and your mass. And this is the stuff that your body uses as building blocks. Anyway, uh that's my thoughts. That's why I want to do this. I think this food is better for you, and I want to make it available because honestly, regeneratively grown food is just not very common. Anyway, thanks.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody, I'm gonna be selling my garden vegetables at the farmer's market soon, and one of the reasons I am doing this is because I feel like my vegetables, my garden vegetables, are qualitatively different.\",\n      \"start\": 0.48,\n      \"end\": 14.24,\n      \"duration\": 13.76,\n      \"confidence\": 0.992,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.48,\n          \"end\": 0.64,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.991\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.64,\n          \"end\": 0.8,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.88,\n          \"end\": 1.04,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 1.04,\n          \"end\": 1.28,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 1.28,\n          \"end\": 1.44,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \",\",\n          \"start\": 1.44,\n          \"end\": 1.6,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.896\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" I\",\n          \"start\": 1.6,\n          \"end\": 1.68,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"'\",\n          \"start\": 1.68,\n          \"end\": 1.76,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.976\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"m\",\n          \"start\": 1.76,\n          \"end\": 1.92,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" g\",\n          \"star